TIL_CLASS_NAME, I'll return the super version. I need to find a loaded class or load it if it isn't already loaded. If I resolve, I'll call resolveClass. For finding classes, if it's only for the target, I’ll use getParent().getResourceAsStream for loading bytes. But what if the parent is null? It’ll throw an IOException. I also need to manage Method.invoke calls, which might add extra dynamic access call sites. I wonder how the TCK will track this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_T541pIKNTgqa0G13gCpBmzxs|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe55d61da8819d90a7c65356365b56", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-hadoop/1.12.2/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 664, "output": 912, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25128, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778275779393, "responseId": "resp_01d3ce057da11f900169fe55c44914819d8aa39541082aa09b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_T541pIKNTgqa0G13gCpBmzxs|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe55d61da8819d90a7c65356365b56", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\": \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"org.apache.parquet.**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\": \"shaded.parquet.it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778275798544}]}
