 only Java9 sites, which seems unfavorable. I wonder if this means we can track cumulatively across attempts. It mentions no changes in the remaining total after previous attempts. I’m thinking about improving the setup to focus purely on legacy. Can we separate original Java9 and legacy tests? I’m not sure if JaCoCo can help, but what if I defined a custom classloader for the instrumented bytes?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adjusting Java runtime path**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether the Java runtime class path is impacted by the module. It seems that maybe the dynamic agent isn’t covering everything since the source line in the duplicate class isn't being mapped properly. It should be! I think I need to include a comment regarding child-first loading. So, it looks like I need to make some edits to address this and ensure everything works smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qYuddjbT8xbfGuuokxrjo1nF|fc_01d3ce057da11f900169fe56dcab38819d8f55d2c6d9f9d749", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-hadoop/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_hadoop/CleanUtilTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\n", "newText": "import java.io.File;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static void invokeCleanDirectBufferFromIsolatedCleanUtil() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader parentClassLoader = CleanUtilTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader classLoader = new IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader(parentClassLoader);\n        Class<?> cleanUtilClass = classLoader.loadClass(CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME);\n        Method cleanDirectBuffer = cleanUtilClass.getMethod(\"cleanDirectBuffer\", ByteBuffer.class);\n        ByteBuffer directBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(32);\n        directBuffer.put((byte) 1);\n        directBuffer.flip();\n\n        try {\n            cleanDirectBuffer.invoke(null, directBuffer);\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n            if (cause instanceof Exception nestedException) {\n                throw nestedException;\n            }\n            if (cause instanceof Error nestedError) {\n                throw nestedError;\n            }\n            throw exception;\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static void invokeCleanDirectBufferFromIsolatedCleanUtil() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader parentClassLoader = CleanUtilTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        try (URLClassLoader classLoader = new IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader(testClasspathUrls(), parentClassLoader)) {\n            Class<?> cleanUtilClass = classLoader.loadClass(CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME);\n            Method cleanDirectBuffer = cleanUtilClass.getMethod(\"cleanDirectBuffer\", ByteBuffer.class);\n            ByteBuffer directBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(32);\n            directBuffer.put((byte) 1);\n            directBuffer.flip();\n\n            try {\n                cleanDirectBuffer.invoke(null, directBuffer);\n            } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n                Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n                if (cause instanceof Exception nestedException) {\n                    throw nestedException;\n                }\n                if (cause instanceof Error nestedError) {\n                    throw nestedError;\n                }\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static URL[] testClasspathUrls() throws Exception {\n        List<URL> urls = new ArrayList<>();\n        for (String entry : System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\").split(File.pathSeparator)) {\n            if (!entry.isBlank()) {\n                urls.add(new File(entry).toURI().toURL());\n            }\n        }\n        return urls.toArray(URL[]::new);\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.findClass(name);\n            }\n\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream classBytes = getParent().getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (classBytes == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n                }\n                byte[] bytes = classBytes.readAllBytes();\n                return defineClass(name, bytes, 0, bytes.length);\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name, exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static final class IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        private IsolatedCleanUtilClassLoader(URL[] urls, ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(urls, parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!CLEAN_UTIL_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1378, "output": 3305, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30795, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778276025373, "responseId": "resp_01d3ce057da11f900169fe56ba45d8819d8475d57dcef9c8a7"}}
